  group_by(Location) %>%
  summarise(prom=mean(StrikeOuts)) %>% 
  ungroup() %>%

  1. Realiza una prueba de permutaciÃ³n para la diferencia de las medias. Grafica la distribuciÃ³n de referencia y calcula el valor p de dos colas.
set.seed(4)
perms_strikeout <- lineup(null_permute("StrikeOuts"), 
                        df%>%select(Location,StrikeOuts), 
                        n = 5000)
decrypt("nsW7 Ykjk l3 gCPljlC3 KJT")
resumen <- perms_strikeout %>% 
  group_by(.sample) %>%
  summarise(dif_home_away = mean(StrikeOuts[Location == "Away"]) - mean(StrikeOuts[Location == "Home"]))

g_1 <- ggplot(resumen, aes(sample = dif_home_away)) + geom_qq(distribution = stats::qunif)  +
  xlab("f") + ylab("diferencia") + labs(subtitle = "DistribuciÃ³n nula o de referencia") +
  geom_hline(yintercept = prom_strikeouts$diferencia, colour = "red") +
  annotate("text", x = 0.35, y = prom_strikeouts$diferencia - 0.03, label = "diferencia observada", colour = "red")

g_2 <- ggplot(resumen, aes(y=dif_home_away)) + 
  geom_histogram() + 
  geom_hline(yintercept = prom_strikeouts$diferencia, 
             linetype ='dashed', color='red')
